cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a machine learning approach for generating synthetic multiple sclerosis (MS) lesions on MRI images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed model is an encoder-decoder U-Net, which is a popular architecture for image segmentation tasks, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses data augmentation, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
